---
description: when user want to implement Hypercho tool tips
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
Hypercho tool tips is a tool tip that can display information when user hover it.

Below is an example:

<HyperchoTooltips value={tooltips.score}>
    <div
    className={`flex items-center gap-1 px-2 py-1 rounded-md cursor-help ${
        ideaData.score >= 80
        ? "bg-green-500/10 text-green-400"
        : ideaData.score >= 60
        ? "bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-400"
        : ideaData.score >= 40
        ? "bg-yellow-500/1 text-yellow-400"
        : "bg-red-500/10 text-red-400"
    }`}
    >
    <span className="font-medium text-sm">
        {ideaData.score}/100
    </span>
    </div>


</HyperchoTooltips>